      "Ingredients": "- 1 lb. ground beef (it makes life a lot easier if you just buy a lean ground beef. Less grease happens that way)\n- 1/2 sweet onion, chopped\n- 1/2 green bell pepper, chopped\n- 1/2 yellow bell pepper, chopped\n- 1/2 orange bell pepper, chopped\n- 3 large T minced garlic, and/or lots of fresh garlic, chopped\n- 1 1/2 cups water\n- 1 15oz. can hunts diced tomatoes \n- 2 8oz. cans hunts tomato sauce \n- Italian seasoning, to taste\n- garlic powder, to taste\n- small amount of salt\n- pepper to taste\n- seasoned salt, to taste \n- 1 bay leaf\n- 1 1/2 T soy sauce\n- 1-2 cups elbow macaroni (if you want it to be a bit more spaghetti-like, use less noodles. But if you don't want it to be super saucy, use more noodles. I like lots of noodles)",
