      "Ingredients": "- 2 cups flour  (If you want to make it healthier and have whole wheat flour you can do 1 cup whole wheat and 1 c reg. flour)\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 1 t salt\n- ½ cup butter, softened (1 stick)\n- 1 cup sugar\n- 2 eggs\n- 1 ½ cup mashed ripe bananas (usually around 3 to 4 bananas depending on how big they are.  I don’t measure.  I just use all the 3 to 4 bananas.  If it’s more than 1 ½ c it hasn’t seemed to matter) \n- ½ tsp vanilla\n- 2/3 c chopped nuts (optional)",
      "Instructions": "- Preheat oven to 350 degrees\n- Spray and flour 2 loaf pans. Set aside\n- Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside\n- Beat butter at medium speed or hand mix until creamy\n- Gradually add sugar and beat well\n- Add eggs one at a time, beat just until yellow disappears after each egg\n- Add vanilla and bananas. Mix just until blended\n- Gradually add flour and beat just until blended. \n- OPTIONAL Stir in nuts if you want them\n- Pour batter into pans BE SURE TO NOT OVER FILL PANS. The batter will rise and fill the entire pan as it bakes\n- Bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean\n- You don’t know how accurate your oven temp is so I would check it after 45 minutes, and then adjust as you need\n- Cool in pans for about 10 minutes\n- Then run knife around the outside of the pans and flip upside down on to plate\n- Do carefully so it comes out whole.  Sometimes I need to wait longer than 10 minutes",
