      "Description": "This is basically a spinach, rice, and cheese casserole, and it's a staple at most of my Wells family functions. It's delicious and I could eat it forever! Give it a try before saying you won't like it :)",
      "Ingredients": "- 1 pkg. 10 oz. chopped spinach cooked and drained\n- 1 cup cooked rice\n- 1 cup shredded sharp cheddar cheese\n- 2 T butter\n- 2 eggs slightly beaten\n- ⅓ cup milk\n- 1 ½ T dried mince onion\n- ½ tsp. Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 tsp. salt \n- ¼ tsp. Rosemary",
      "Instructions": "- Combine all ingredients together\n- Pour into a greased 10x6x1½  baking dish\n- Bake at 350°F for 25 minutes\n\n- For our large get togethers, I double this and put in a large pan\n- Use a13x9 and it’s just thicker\n- It will most likely need to cook a bit longer",
