      "Description": "I know it sounds terrible, but it's just beef and it's the only meatloaf I'll ever eat. It actually tastes very good! Don't knock it 'til you try it.",
      "Ingredients": "- 2 ½ lbs. Ground sirloin\n- 1 cup seasoned bread crumbs\n- 3 eggs\n- 1 small onion diced\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 2 cloves garlic crushed\n- 1 tsp pepper\n- 1 tsp dry mustard\n- 2 tsp Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- BBQ sauce (maybe a ½ c) this depends on the feel when you mix it. It may not need that much. This is the last thing I mix in. And I do a little at a time. If you put in too much it won’t stick together and will be too runny. But you need some moisture.\n- Ketchup (Just to put on top of the meatloaf before you bake it)",
      "Instructions": "- Mix all the ingredients together except sirloin, barbecue sauce and ketchup\n- Once it’s all combined add sirloin. mix with your hands. It's the only way to get the crumb mixture thoroughly combined \n- Add the barbecue sauce until you feel it has the right consistency\n- Put in roasting pan and pat together \n- Pour Ketchup on top and spread around\n- Bake at 350 degrees for 1 to 1 ½ hours",
